title: PPPP Candidate Mir Naseebullah Khan wins PB-09 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians (PPPP) candidate Mir NaseebUllah Khan has won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-09, Kohlu by securing 5,888 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an Independent candidate Gazain Khan Marri who bagged 3,351 votes.
Overall voters’ turnout remained 25.36 percent.
